<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-06-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-06-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="922" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d922">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/7754</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Consul <persName type="to">Dawson</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-06-01">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 1, 1916</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Standard Oil Company has kindly offered to place at your disposal for
                            American refugees any of its steamers in Tampico harbor in case of
                            emergency. Should case of urgency arise, do not hesitate to make request
                            of company’s representative. Company requests following confidential
                            telegram be delivered to I. S. Broun, its shipping agent at Tampico: “We
                            approve granting Consul’s request. D. T. Warden.”</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>